<DOC><DOCNO> AP880806-0071 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-06-88 2246EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-China-Flood     08-06 0152</FIRST><SECOND>AM-China-Flood,0157</SECOND><HEAD>Flooding Kills At Least 21 In North China</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Torrential rains flooded 40 villages in northChina and killed at least 21 people, the official Xinhua NewsAgency said Saturday.   Xinhua's brief report said 19 other people were missingfollowing a 3{-hour deluge Saturday morning in Fenyang County inShanxi province.   About 30,000 people were marooned by the flood waters, and atleast 100 houses were destroyed, it said.   No details were given on rescue efforts in the latest of aseries of natural disasters to hit China this year.   Most recent official figures on flash flooding a week ago incoastal Zhejiang province put the death toll at 256, with 316people missing.   More than 500 other people have died throughout China inseparate floods, hailstorms and a typhoon this year, while a heatwave in June and July claimed nearly 500 lives in central cities.</TEXT></DOC>